{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike standard prompts, which typically present a single-step instruction, CoT prompts encourage the model to generate a sequence of interconnected thoughts or explanations that lead to the final answer.",
    "This approach mirrors human reasoning, where solving complex problems often involves considering multiple factors or steps in a logical order.",
    "The prompt template of the chain-of-thought is provided in Appendix A.",
    "Automatic Prompt EngineeringAutomatic Prompt Engineering (APE) [56] refers to a method where language models automatically generate and refine prompts without human intervention.",
    "This approach treats prompt creation as a process of generating and improving instructions using the model's inherent capabilities."
  ]
}